Dusseldorf is a hub for the telecommunications industry, and Singapore is a hub for the finance

107
00:07:05,420 --> 00:07:06,420
industry.

108
00:07:06,420 --> 00:07:10,740
In addition to the ability to tap into a common labor pool, businesses cluster because they

109
00:07:10,740 --> 00:07:14,460
want easy access to other businesses.

110
00:07:14,460 --> 00:07:19,020
Telecommunications companies like Vodafone, Deutsche Telekom, and AT&T all exist as direct

111
00:07:19,020 --> 00:07:23,340
competitors in Dusseldorf but the reason they are there is because other companies exist

112
00:07:23,340 --> 00:07:25,680
there as well that they can work with.

113
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:30,080
You and Dusseldorf are companies like Nokia, Google, and LG which each make the phones

114
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:33,080
that the mobile service providers might stock in their stores.

115
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:36,880
By all being in the same place, they can more easily collaborate and therefore they can

116
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:38,840
run their businesses more efficiently.

117
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:43,120
There's a sort of economies of scale effect when all sorts of companies are all packed

118
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,960
together in one place.

119
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:50,260
Now, not every business is in a city because there are plenty of cases where the minuses

120
00:07:50,260 --> 00:07:52,080
outweigh the pluses.

121
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:56,840
You just won't see a car manufacturing plant in downtown Manhattan because it doesn't

122
