134
00:08:43,460 --> 00:08:45,740
Cities exist because they are efficient.

135
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:50,180
Nobody's forcing individuals to move to cities, but billions have.

136
00:08:50,180 --> 00:08:54,040
Just imagine there were only ten people in existence and one product that each of them

137
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,280
wanted to buy.

138
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:59,920
If they were all equally spread out across this plain, the logical location for a distribution

139
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:02,000
hub would be right in the center.

140
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:06,260
Some individuals would happen to be close to the hub by chance, but overall the product

141
00:09:06,260 --> 00:09:10,360
would have to be shipped a large distance to get to every consumer.

142
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:15,060
Now let's say that eight of those ten individuals lived together in a mini-city.

143
00:09:15,060 --> 00:09:19,620
The logical location for the distribution hub would then be right by the city.

144
00:09:19,620 --> 00:09:23,960
Shipping for the rural individuals would be slow and expensive, but overall the total

145
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:27,280
shipping distance and cost to individuals would be lower.

146
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:31,420
You can see this concept with where Amazon puts their warehouses in the UK.

147
00:09:31,420 --> 00:09:36,060
They could have one enormous warehouse at the geographic center of the country and save

148
00:09:36,060 --> 00:09:38,840
money through economies of scale, but they don't.

149
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:43,800
They position each of their warehouses near major population centers to reduce the total

150
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,200
shipping distance.

